      "automation_source": "clawsweeper",
      "repair_reason": "This is a draft, protected, security-sensitive policy/runtime PR with a concrete blocker and explicit maintainer architecture questions, so it should stay in human review rather than the cleanup lane.; Needs attention: The diff introduces a trusted runtime policy gate, and the current activation check can silently leave that gate unenforced for a normally enabled policy plugin.; Review finding: [P2] Honor plugin ena... (sha=bd60f2090af051e8323530241b352993f06b179e)",
      "review_summary": "The PR adds bundled policy tool metadata checks, doctor lint integration, oc-path document APIs, policy attestations, and an optional trusted-tool runtime gate.\n\nReproducibility: yes. source-reproducible. With `plugins.entries.policy.enabled=true` and `plugins.entries.policy.config.runtimeToolPolicy=true` but no `config.enabled`, `evaluatePolicyTrustedToolCall` returns before loading policy even though the documented enable flow and health registration treat the plugin as enabled.",
